verbs.description: domify (third-person singular simple present domifies, present participle domifying, simple past and past participle domified)

entries.meaning: (astrology, obsolete) To divide (the heavens) into different astrological houses.
examples: There are various ways of domifying. That of Regiomontanus, which is the most common, makes the circles of position pass through the intersections of the meridian and the horizon; but others make them pass through the poles of the zodiac.
